                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Director of the Policy Planning Staff</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nitze</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-14">November 14,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Policy Planning Staff has given a
                    great deal of time and thought to the attached document. It would be very
                    helpful to us if, after you have had a chance to read it, you could find a few
                    minutes to give the Staff your reactions.<note n="1" xml:id="d134fn1">The source
                        text bears the following marginal notation by Secretary of State Acheson: “I
                        have read all of this with great interest.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paul H. Nitze</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
